CNCP v1 22919
{
  "concept": "vuejs/core#7179: Support `browser` export condition out-of-the-box.",
  "version": "1.0",
  "created_at": "2026-03-15T04:25:25.458069+00:00",
  "text": "Support `browser` export condition out-of-the-box.\n\n### What problem does this feature solve?\n\nWhen using `vue` with a bundler such as `esbuild`, we need to manually configure an alias pointing from `vue` to `vue/dist/vue.esm-bundler.js` to get support for the runtime compiler. By adding a browser [export condition](https://nodejs.org/dist/latest-v18.x/docs/api/packages.html#conditional-exports), tool which supports conditional exports like `esbuild` can bundle `vue` with the \r\ncorrect mapping automatically.\n\n### What does the proposed API look like?\n\nNo new API will be added, but some additional metadata in `vue/package.json`:\r\n\r\n```json\r\n{\r\n  \"exports\": {\r\n    \".\": {\r\n      \"browser\": {\r\n        \"import\": \"./dist/vue.esm-browser.js\" // or \"./dist/vue.esm-browser.prod.js\", minified bundle by default\r\n      },\r\n      // ... other export conditions for \"vue\" entry\r\n     }\r\n  }\r\n}\r\n```",
  "language": "en",
  "keywords": [
    ":sparkles: feature request"
  ],
  "embedding": {
